    },
    {
      "id": "el_11",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1005,
      "y": 125,
      "width": 312,
      "height": 203,
      "text": "Daily wage = Total payment / Days worked\n\nPiece rate = Payment per unit produced\nTotal pay = Units × Rate per unit\n\nContractor pay:\n  Total cost = Σ(workers × rate × days)\n\nWHY: Daily wage assumes equal work each\nday. Piece rate pays per output instead.\n\nEx: 15 men × 12 days, paid Rs.54000\n  Daily wage = 54000/(15×12) = Rs.300",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 1100,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 11,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Daily wage = Total payment / Days worked\n\nPiece rate = Payment per unit produced\nTotal pay = Units × Rate per unit\n\nContractor pay:\n  Total cost = Σ(workers × rate × days)\n\nWHY: Daily wage assumes equal work each\nday. Piece rate pays per output instead.\n\nEx: 15 men × 12 days, paid Rs.54000\n  Daily wage = 54000/(15×12) = Rs.300",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
